# Draven voice policy (JonBeatz)

## Default voices

| Priority | Engine | When |
|----------|--------|------|
| **Primary** | **OmniVoice** (British male, CPU) | Every allowed speak |
| **Backup** | Edge `en-GB-RyanNeural` | Only if OmniVoice fails |

## When to speak (allowed)

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| **Start Project** ritual | `npm run draven:speak -- "..."` once (greeting) |
| **End Project** ritual | `npm run draven:speak -- "..."` once (short farewell) |
| Jon says **speak**, **say**, **talk this**, **read aloud** | `npm run draven:speak -- "<exact text>"` |
| Critical **Mem0 / stack errors** | Only if `DRAVEN_VOICE_ERRORS=1` (default on) |

## When NOT to speak

- **Never** read ordinary chat replies or summaries aloud.
- **Never** speak after `mem0:add`, `mem0:search`, or successful Mem0 recall.
- **Never** auto-speak Hermes Desktop / Telegram agent responses (`auto_tts: false` in Hermes config).
- **Never** start OmniVoice daemon at PC boot — lazy start on first ritual speak; stop on End Project.

## Commands

```powershell
npm run draven:speak -- "text"   # OmniVoice (Ryan fallback on failure)
npm run draven:omni-daemon       # optional pre-warm before Start Project
npm run draven:omni-daemon -- -Stop  # free RAM (also runs on session:stop)
```

`jarvis:*` aliases deprecated — use `draven:*` equivalents.

See **`.cursor/docs/VOICE-WORKFLOW.md`** for errors, fixes, and resource notes.
